was created by American writer L. Ron Hubbard (1911-1986) in May 1952.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2292, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999917249625, \"rank\": 4.123445171872182e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2308, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"score\": 0.9805175841357983, \"rank\": 0.019869490567581624, \"text\": \"L.\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\"}, {\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Ron_Hubbard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816057466416323e-37, \"text\": \"Hubbard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Ron_Hubbard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Ron_Hubbard\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Scientology\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2276}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Initially Hubbard created a program of ideas known as mental, whose documents and materials were distributed by the Mentalism Foundation.\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mentalism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.541926735519186e-28, \"text\": \"Mentalism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mentalism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mentalism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hubbard\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2365}, {\"ngram\": \"a program\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2383}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"whose documents\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"materials\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The foundation was soon bankrupted and Hubbard lost rights to the Dianetics project: The Modern Science of Mental Health (Dental Health): The Modern Science of Mental Health) in 1952.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2525, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Ron_Hubbard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816057466416323e-37, \"text\": \"Hubbard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Ron_Hubbard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Ron_Hubbard\"}, {\"begin\": 2552, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dianetics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dianetics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dianetics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dianetics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The foundation\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2544}, {\"ngram\": \"The Modern Science\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2589}, {\"ngram\": \"Mental Health\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2606}, {\"ngram\": \"Dental Health\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"The Modern Science\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"Mental Health\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hubbard re-charted the subject of intellectual in religion and renamed it Scientology, maintaining terminology, doctrines, electronic measure (E-meter) and the practice of auditing.\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scientology\", \"score\": 0.9999996420484153, \"rank\": 3.579516646847505e-07, \"text\": \"Scientology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scientology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scientology\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the subject\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2700}, {\"ngram\": \"intellectual\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2716}, {\"ngram\": \"religion\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2728}, {\"ngram\": \"terminology\", \"from\": 2769, \"to\": 2780}, {\"ngram\": \"doctrines\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2791}, {\"ngram\": \"electronic measure\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"E\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2814}, {\"ngram\": \"meter\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"auditing\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 2850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within a year, he regained rights over intellectual works and retained the two subjects under the umbrella of the Church of Scientology.\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2988, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a year\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2865}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2885}, {\"ngram\": \"intellectual works\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"the two subjects\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"the umbrella\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 2958}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"Scientology\", \"from\": 2976, \"to\": 2987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Church of Scientology says that man is an immortal, spiritual being (thetan) who inhabits a physical body.\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Church\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"Scientology\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3014}, {\"ngram\": \"that man\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3028}, {\"ngram\": \"an immortal, spiritual being\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3060}, {\"ngram\": \"a physical body\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The thetan had countless past lives and according to the advanced texts of scientology the lives that preceded the coming of the thetan to Earth were lived in alien cultures.\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The thetan\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3110}, {\"ngram\": \"countless past lives\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3135}, {\"ngram\": \"t